SimpleSock README
-----------------

1.) About

This library is a conventient little abstraction to help with using BSD sockets
under Unix-based OSes, and WinSock under Windows.


2.) Installation and Usage

See the file INSTALL for installation instructions.

To use the library in an application, use the preprocessor directive

#include <simplesock/SimpleSock.h>

and add "-lsimplesock" to the compiler options to link with the static library.


3.) License

This library is licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPL).
See the file COPYING for details.

Most of the code is based on information from the official WinSock documentation,
and Beej's Guide to Network Programming <http://beej.us/guide/bgnet/>
